His perspective on race relations in relationships was criticized in a column by Quynh Nguyen titled http://media.www.californiaaggie.com/media/storage/paper981/news/2004/02/13/Features/DoesRace.Matter.In.Love1316484.shtml Does Race Matter in Love? (along with a taste of his sophisticated racial and gender terminology, such as Yella womenz, White Rice Kings, and slanted for extra Oriental sensation.)

For Winter 2006 quarter, Hamamoto is teaching ASA 140 (Asian American Media) and ASA 150B (Japanese American Experiences).


